  "day": 57,
  "key": "day_57_davids_lord",
  "version": 1,
  "updated_at": "2026-02-17",
  "title": {
    "en": "David Calls Him Lord"
  },
  "intro": {
    "en": [
      "While teaching in Jerusalem, Jesus asked a question about the Messiah.",
      "He referred to the words of the Prophet David."
    ]
  },
  "blocks": {
    "en": [
      {
        "type": "text",
        "marker": "question",
        "icon": "help",
        "label": { "en": "Whose Son Is the Messiah?" },
        "lines": [
          "Jesus asked,",
          "“How is it that they say",
          "the Christ is David’s son?”"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "marker": "psalm",
        "icon": "menu_book",
        "label": { "en": "The Lord Said to My Lord" },
        "lines": [
          "“For David himself says",
          "in the book of Psalms:",
          "‘The LORD said to my Lord,",
          "Sit at my right hand",
          "until I make your enemies",
          "a footstool for your feet.’”"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "marker": "authority",
        "icon": "gavel",
        "label": { "en": "More Than a Son" },
        "lines": [
          "Jesus said,",
          "“David calls him ‘Lord.’",
          "How then can he be his son?”"
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
  "question": {
    "en": "If David calls the Messiah ‘Lord,’ what does this suggest about the Messiah’s identity?"
  },
  "further_reading": {
    "en": ["Luke 20:41–44", "Psalm 110:1"]
  }
}
